Description: To indicate a unique number at BAR 0 + 0x0 location for Bridge Discovery
To indicate that this is the last bridge in the Bridge Discovery

Note: Current value of Bridge version is 0x0100

Description:
0X0 : AXI3 Bridge in Master Mode
0x1 : AXI3 Bridge in Slave Mode
0x2 : AXI4 Bridge in Master Mode
0x3 : AXI4 Bridge in Slave Mode
0x4: AXI4-Lite Bridge in Master Mode
0x5: AXI4-Lite Bridge in Slave Mode
0x6: AXI4-Stream Bridge in Master Mode
0x7: AXI4-Stream Bridge in Slave Mode
0x8 : ACE Bridge in Master Mode 
0x9: ACE Bridge in Slave Mode
0xA: CHI Bridge in RN_F Mode
0xB: CHI Bridge in HN_F Mode
0XC: CXS Bridge

TX Ownership bit for CXS bridge, it is set when Flit is sent on TX channel when TX Ownership Flip bits are programmed.
This field is Clear on Read.
SW asserts this bit to 1 to indicate HW bridge can start issuing corresponding transaction on TX Channel on CXS bridge at DUT interface.

RX Ownership bit for CXS bridge, it is set when Flit is received  on RX channel. 
This field is Clear by corresponding Ownership Flip bit from SW.
Set by software  when RX buffer has been read by software .This bit clears the corresponding OWNERSHIP bit.
When a Good TLP within Flit is received, the particular bit is set, it is cleared by Corresponding Ownership Flip Bit from SW.
When a Error TLP within Flit is received, the particular bit is set, it is cleared by Corresponding Ownership Flip Bit from SW.

0 = disables interrupt generation if any FLIT_TXN bit in INTR_FLIT_TXN_STATUS_REG is set
